# Skipr agent guide

Skipr detects in-video ad reads on YouTube. The skipr-plugin Firefox extension calls a Flask API; the server fetches transcripts, classifies chunks with DistilBERT, and returns skip timestamps/intervals.

```
skipr-plugin/         Firefox extension (client)
server/               Flask API, ML pipeline, database
server/backend/       SQLAlchemy models + data access (v2)
server/migrations/    Alembic schema revisions
tests/                All tests (never colocate under server/ or skipr-plugin/)
```

## Tests

- Add tests under `tests/`, grouped by component:
  - `tests/server/ml/` — transcript labelling, org extraction
  - `tests/server/utils/` — URL parsing, helpers
  - `tests/server/backend/` — stores, models, persistence
  - `tests/server/api/` — Flask routes and request/response
  - `tests/skipr-plugin/` — extension scripts
- Use `tests/support/path.py` to import from `server/`; do not duplicate path hacks in each file.
- Run from repo root: `PYTHONPATH=. python -m unittest discover -s tests -p "test_*.py"`

### Run tests on code changes

After any code change, run the matching test suite before finishing. Fix failures caused by your change; do not leave broken tests.

| Changed area | Command |
|---|---|
| Any server change (default) | `PYTHONPATH=. python -m unittest discover -s tests -p "test_*.py"` |
| `server/transcript_labelling.py`, `server/org_extractor.py` | `PYTHONPATH=. python -m unittest discover -s tests/server/ml -p "test_*.py"` |
| `server/youtube_url.py`, `server/app.py` (validation) | `PYTHONPATH=. python -m unittest discover -s tests/server/utils -p "test_*.py"` |
| `server/backend/` | `PYTHONPATH=. python -m unittest discover -s tests/server/backend -p "test_*.py"` |
| `skipr-plugin/` | `PYTHONPATH=. python -m unittest discover -s tests/skipr-plugin -p "test_*.py"` |

If you add or modify behavior, add or update tests in the matching `tests/` subfolder in the same change.

- **New functions require unit tests** in the matching `tests/` subfolder in the same change.
- **All unit tests must pass** before finishing; fix failures caused by your change.

### Static checks

After Python changes, run mypy and autopep8 from repo root. Fix any failures caused by your change before finishing.

**autopep8** (PEP 8 formatting):

```bash
./run.sh autopep8-check
```

**mypy** (typing / static analysis):

```bash
./run.sh mypy
```

## Architecture

- **API** (`/api/v2/timestamps`): `server/backend/` (`IntervalStore`, SQLAlchemy). Status-based polling (`pending` / `ready` / `failed`).
- **ML**: `transcript_labelling.py` (batched DistilBERT, NER on ad windows only), `org_extractor.py`. Models load at import time; auto-selects CUDA/MPS/CPU.
- **Schema**: Alembic is source of truth. Add migrations in `server/migrations/versions/`; do not define tables in `initdb/schema.sql`.
- **Startup**: `entrypoint.sh` → `alembic upgrade head` → `gunicorn`.

## Coding requirements

- Minimal diff only; no unrelated refactors or over-engineering.
- Match existing naming, layout, imports, and abstraction level.
- Thin route handlers; persistence in `server/backend/` stores.
- Type hints on all new functions and methods; mypy must pass.
- SQLAlchemy ORM for all DB access; no raw SQL in route handlers.
- Alembic migration for every schema change; idempotent when possible.
- **Every new function** gets a brief inline comment (or docstring) at the top describing what it does.
- Elsewhere, comments only for non-obvious logic.
- **Logging**: when adding or touching key control flows (API routes, store decisions, background jobs, pipeline steps), add `info` / `warning` / `error` logs as appropriate. Use `logging.getLogger(__name__)`; do not use `print`.
- **New functions require unit tests** in the matching `tests/` subfolder.
- Always run the relevant test suite after code changes (see **Run tests on code changes**); all tests must pass.
- Run mypy and autopep8 after Python changes (see **Static checks**); fix violations caused by your change.
- Never commit `.env`, credentials, or tokens.
- Do not commit, push, or amend unless the user explicitly asks.

## Review before finishing

- [ ] Scoped to the request; no drive-by edits
- [ ] Matches surrounding code and `server/backend/` patterns
- [ ] Schema changes include an Alembic migration
- [ ] No secrets, debug prints, or dead commented code
- [ ] v2 DB access via `backend/`, not ad-hoc SQL in `app.py`
- [ ] New functions have an inline comment/docstring describing behavior
- [ ] Key control flows touched include appropriate `info` / `warning` / `error` logs
- [ ] New functions have unit tests under `tests/` in the correct subfolder
- [ ] Relevant test suite run and all tests passing
- [ ] `./run.sh autopep8-check` passes (or only pre-existing failures explained)
- [ ] `./run.sh mypy` passes (or only pre-existing failures explained)

When unsure, read `app.py`, `server/backend/`, and `transcript_labelling.py` first.
